@Weiming123, transfer the ISO to a DVD or a USB flash drive using the Microsoft USB/DVD Download Tool (google it for the link) or use the Universal USB Installer or YUMI which can be found at pendrivelinux.com

Follow the instructions from there. After the preparation of the flash drive, boot from it (your BIOS should be set to boot from it), follow the menu and complete the installation. After installing, run the Windows Loader to activate it.

If you still cannot follow these very simple steps then you need serious help.

